    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-06-25T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-06-25T03:00:00-05:00" n="878"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d878">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">661.1115/85: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at London</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-06-25T09:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 25, 1920—9 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 25—7:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Invited to attend meeting of the Permanent Committee of Supreme Economic Council
                    at 11 o’clock tomorrow morning, Saturday.</p>
                <p>Krassin and other Russian delegates will be present. Unless I am instructed to
                    the contrary immediately I shall advise Committee that I cannot be present.
                    Embassy informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Skinner</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
